[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating testing methods**\n\nIt's interesting that AntTest uses reflection MethodHandles for invoking synthetic classes in tests. The user prefers not to use reflection directly unless it's necessary. For the active class, I think we could cover functionality via the public API instead. Maybe I can add two tests that involve a public API—one for the context loader and another specifically for getResourceSource. Overall, I need to make sure everything is version-agnostic and doesn’t rely on direct reflection.\n\n**Examining native image classloading**\n\nIt seems that the native image classloader isn’t typical. I need to understand how tests pass multiple getResourceAsStream calls on test classes. In a native image, reachability metadata might be included, but library class resources could be missing unless specified. I wonder if I can use a resource present in test resources. For the assertion, can I ensure a non-null result when getting a resource? The resource must be on the runtime classpath, accessible via the java.class.path runtime argument. I'll need to take a closer look at the Locator source.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a5db0cb0aaf79500169f592100e0c8197b995d9612e084e40\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9ZIXZLGR_OQ06pyP2IOiuRiDvMckfTcHC4wo3oLFKGLkBaS_0KcLAcl6s_seoQS72fFanMG4rLiFpu5EDeFuXFWmqgugyAUpRgr9zdxCJSnxLjVc1zzr6vUP-KzPICyKocmIeY7vhAEsaxRfhSJzywME8FLIvKu-E_1IQqnLNL9VfYgd4TbKzTbXRROx9kKCECDy0QFxyPFd9tfvCiCSz3mo_89oUTJdfvzGHijihD_LaDju_RYkwonYeRN7Ak655LECLuA79m-0HtosSy67nJZ2YgDxb78QcGpuDMCezYHfbS3vxhtjEEioCd1hfWf-L4JjJCIKc5js3qdTjbXXrJpG4txB8OpbXqOMsFUmjgh9icFb0sSTovoC7IQmy6dXN93pg9Vyi-7cqv_V4pHHIflq9N5b-OYvsDPOcJzE6ChJNepQWPDR6VQhN_yXite1MdVnUMzBqLrxYK66bYS39YkMumoWUHS2ZD3XdTfJ60PZXX4h38OQVjySti2Ui1dlDvgUnBex4YgUv63OJfciWQtZW3e7di8OST8E2pTK-sERdJwxbGSoNFeRla2VFFiUhH0H2aLjkgzNxiC3_u4ECFEM2zf9wNMD21s8SygtQqD7f